    <Data><![CDATA[<h1>Applies to</h1>
  <p>All web applications.<br /></p>
  <h1>What to Do</h1>
  <p>Consider the threats to stored data.</p>
  <h1>Why</h1>
  <p>Consider the threats to stored data to help make decisions about how to encrypt stored data.</p>
  <h1>How</h1>
  <p>To consider the threats to stored data:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Identify sensitive data.</strong>&amp;nbsp;Make a list of assets that should be protected with encryption.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Identify threats to sensitive data.</strong>&amp;nbsp;Make a list of types of threats to stored sensitive data. For example: insider attacks, external attacks, organized crime, industrial espionage, etc.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        <strong>Identify solutions.</strong>&amp;nbsp;For each asset that should be protected with encryption, identify a software solution that offers strong encryption.</p>
    </li>
  </ol>
